  <div class="box">
    <h3>Challenges</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Data can be hard to interpret if it is not presented in a thoughtful and structured way. Information should be presented in context and be unbiased as possible.</li>
      <li>Information can be overwhelming if too much is presented at once.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Opportunities</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Enable greater user engagement through a playful, empathetic approach to visually dense information through custom, interactive maps.</li>
      <li>Encourage users to explore and discover information across different geographic contexts.</li>
      <li>Allow the client to manage all their data and modify the information presented using reusable custom components.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <figure class="media image">
    <img loading="lazy" src="/assets/work/florida-dashboard/florida-dashboard_005.png" alt="Example of comparative graph" />
    <figcaption>Example of comparative graphs, with a custom geography quick selector, focusing on contrast and readability</figcaption>
